100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 27, 1925, the British government announced a significant increase in coal production to address the ongoing miners' strike, aimed at stabilizing the economy. In the United States, the trial of John Scopes, charged with teaching evolution in Tennessee, continued to draw national attention, igniting debates on science and religion. Meanwhile, in Europe, tensions rose as France and Germany grappled with reparations issues stemming from World War I, complicating diplomatic relations.
